header.name: Over-encoding
header.description: Any instance in which more encoding than the default is employed to refer to an active participant or prop. Over-encoding is used in Greek, as in other languages: to mark the beginning of a narrative unit (e.g. Mt 4:5); and to highlight the action or speech concerned (e.g. Mt 4:7).
